main event: A military observer reported a sighting of a slow-moving, intermittently pulsating star-like object over the Eastern Mediterranean on August 30, 1958.
interesting points: The sighting was documented in a Project 10073 record card., The observation was classified as visual and sourced from military personnel., The object was described as resembling a 'Sputnik-like' silhouette., Conclusions drawn included the possibilities of it being a balloon, a satellite, an aircraft, or an astronomical object., The number of objects observed was one, but the length of observation was not given.
sighted object: slow moving, intermittently pulsating star-like object
